{{Infobox language family |name=Monumbo |altname=Bogia Bay |region=[[Madang Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]] |familycolor=Papuan |family=a possible primary [[language family]] |child1=[[Monumbo language|Monumbo]] |child2=[[Lilau language|Lilau]] |glotto=monu1249 |glottorefname=Monumbo }}
The '''Monumbo''' languages, [[Monumbo language|Monumbo]] and the closely related [[Lilau language|Lilau]], constitute a small language family on the north coast of Papua New Guinea. They have for several decades been lumped into the [[Torricelli languages|Torricelli]] family 100&nbsp;km to the west, but "no evidence [for this] was ever presented".<ref>[http://glottolog.org/resource/languoid/id/monu1249 Glottolog: Monumbo]</ref>
