{{distinguish|Tonga language (disambiguation){{!}}Tonga language}} {{Infobox language |name=Maniq |altname=Tonga |nativename=''Ten'edn'' |states=[[Thailand]], [[Malaysia]] |region= |ethnicity=[[Maniq people]] |speakers=365 |date=2007-2014 |ref=<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/tnz|title=Ten’edn|work=Ethnologue|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en}}</ref> |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Aslian languages|Aslian]] |fam3=[[Jahaic languages|Jahaic]] |fam4= |iso3=tnz |glotto=tong1308 |glottorefname=Tonga (Thailand) }}
The [[Mani people|Maniq]] language '''''Ten'edn''''', known in some of the previous literature as '''Tonga''', is an aboriginal [[Mon–Khmer language]] of Thailand and Malaya. It goes by the name Mos in Thailand, which it shares with [[Kensiu language|Kensiu]]. (The name Maniq is also shared with Kensiu.)
According to Benjamin (2012), Maniq (Məniʔ, Maniʔ) can refer to the following three or more speech varieties. *Tonga' (Toŋaʔ) *Mos (Mɔs) *Teanean (Ten'en, Tɛnʔɛn, Tean-ean)
